<chapter id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>

<!-- The introduction chapter contains a brief introduction for the
application that explains what it does and where to report
problems. Basically a long version of the abstract.  Don't include a
revision history. (see installation appendix comment) -->

<para>
&bookcase; is a program for managing collections. It began as a simple
book collection manager, and has expanded to include default
collection templates for bibliographies, comic books, videos, music,
coins, stamps, trading cards, and wines. In addition, custom
collections can be built for any other type of collectibles.
</para>

<sect1 id="what-bookcase-is">
<title>What &bookcase; Is</title>

<para> &bookcase; keeps track of the items in a collection, and offers
an easy way to enter data for each entry. It provides several
different field types, and allows for an unlimited number of
user-defined fields. The entries in a collection may be grouped by any
field for easy organization, and customizable views show as much or as
little information as you like. Full text searching is available, as
well as filtering to show a subset of your collection.
</para>

<para>
Collections may be imported or exported using a variety of formats, to
to allow for easy exchange or publication of data.
</para>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="what-bookcase-is-not">
<title>What &bookcase; Is Not</title>

<para>
&bookcase; is not an audio or video player. It does not provide
facilities for reading or modifying multimedia files. It also does
not provide any image-editing functionality.
</para>

</sect1>

</chapter>

