<para>
In order to successfully use &bookcase;, you need KDE 3.1.x.
&bookcase; uses about 5 megabytes of memory to run, but this may vary
depending on your platform and configuration.
</para>

<para>
&kde; can be found at <ulink url="http://www.kde.org">the KDE home page</ulink>.
</para>

