<sect1 id="compilation">
<title>Compilation and Installation</title>

<para>
In order to compile and install &bookcase; on your system, type the following
in the base directory of the archive, where the third step must be done as
root if you are installing in a system directory:

<screen width="40">
<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput>./configure --enable-final --disable-debug</userinput>
<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput>make</userinput>
<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput>make install</userinput>
</screen>
</para>

<para>Since &bookcase; uses autoconf and automake you should not have
any trouble compiling it. Should you run into problems please report
them to the the author at <email>&email;</email>.</para>

</sect1>

